      "q": "How much federal contract money goes to Vermont?",
      "a": "The state has received $321M in federal contract obligations in FY2026 to date. Total award activity includes 3,516 awards with an average award size of $91.3K. Annual obligations by fiscal year are FY21 $394M, FY22 $506M, FY23 $424M, FY24 $920M, FY25 $877M, and FY26 $321M."
    },
    {
      "q": "Which agencies award the most contracts in Vermont?",
      "a": "The Department of Defense ($202M) and the Department of Veterans Affairs ($51.2M) award the most contracts in Vermont in FY2026 to date. The Department of Homeland Security follows with $33.7M, then the Department of Labor with $12M and the General Services Administration with $6.1M."
